00:36:16.280 --> 00:36:19.810
This system undergoes
a time evolution

00:36:19.810 --> 00:36:22.360
to a state which is
rather complicated.

00:36:22.360 --> 00:36:25.990
But if you make
the number n large,

00:36:25.990 --> 00:36:31.450
this becomes
approximately a state

00:36:31.450 --> 00:36:33.340
where you have
simply-- you know what

00:36:33.340 --> 00:36:34.840
the rate of the
semiclassical limit?

00:36:34.840 --> 00:36:37.680
In the semiclassical limit,
we have a constant laser beam

00:36:37.680 --> 00:36:40.090
with constant electric
field amplitude, e,

00:36:40.090 --> 00:36:42.130
and then we have driven
Rabi oscillations

00:36:42.130 --> 00:36:45.800
between ground
and excited state.

00:36:45.800 --> 00:36:48.900
So therefore, I don't want
to show you mathematically,

00:36:48.900 --> 00:36:52.770
but in the limit of large
n, you can approximate

00:36:52.770 --> 00:36:55.570
this complicated
entangled wave function

00:36:55.570 --> 00:36:58.470
by the product of
Rabi oscillations

00:36:58.470 --> 00:37:03.180
between ground and excited state
times a coherent photon field.

00:37:07.040 --> 00:37:11.240
And the correction
between what I just said

00:37:11.240 --> 00:37:17.470
and this complicated wave
function is like 1 over n,

00:37:17.470 --> 00:37:20.900
because it's sort of a
1 over n approximation

00:37:20.900 --> 00:37:22.810
where we have
neglected terms which

00:37:22.810 --> 00:37:27.040
the relative importance
of them is 1 over n.

00:37:27.040 --> 00:37:31.000
So therefore, there
are people who will say

00:37:31.000 --> 00:37:33.380
and who will tell
you when we have

00:37:33.380 --> 00:37:36.470
an interaction of an atom
with a coherent state,

00:37:36.470 --> 00:37:41.010
and let's just think in the
number of n being large,

00:37:41.010 --> 00:37:46.260
that n times out of n plus
1, we have a coherent state.

00:37:46.260 --> 00:37:48.110
The atom does Rabi
oscillation and what

00:37:48.110 --> 00:37:51.410
it does is it just emits
photon into the coherent field

00:37:51.410 --> 00:37:54.760
and takes it back, like
in semiclassical physics.

00:37:54.760 --> 00:38:00.030
But in one case out of
n cases, or the rate

00:38:00.030 --> 00:38:03.302
1 over n of the rate of the
wave function is sort of fuzzy.

00:38:03.302 --> 00:38:05.010
It's not a coherent
state; it's something

00:38:05.010 --> 00:38:06.840
much more complicated.

00:38:06.840 --> 00:38:11.160
And if you do not keep track
of this complicated nature

00:38:11.160 --> 00:38:15.192
of the wave function and just
do some simple measurement by,

00:38:15.192 --> 00:38:16.650
let's say, just
measuring the phase

00:38:16.650 --> 00:38:19.195
of the electromagnetic
wave by projecting

00:38:19.195 --> 00:38:21.970
onto a coherent
state, then you would

00:38:21.970 --> 00:38:26.750
find that with the
probability of n

00:38:26.750 --> 00:38:29.590
the system was just staying
in a coherent state.

00:38:29.590 --> 00:38:32.770
And with a probability
which is one part out of n,

00:38:32.770 --> 00:38:37.315
something else has happened,
and your detector cannot capture

00:38:37.315 --> 00:38:39.680
the entanglement of that state.

00:38:39.680 --> 00:38:42.550
And this last part
is what some people

00:38:42.550 --> 00:38:44.370
associate with
spontaneous emission.

00:38:47.050 --> 00:38:48.080
I don't know.

00:38:48.080 --> 00:38:51.920
That's my view where the
